  "texts": [
    "Suggested measures include improving content moderation, algorithmic accountability, advertisement and recommender systems, internal processes, third-party auditing, etc.",
    "( Article 35).",
    "Ps must also submit to independent risk assessment audits, share additional data and algorithms for closer regulatory scrutiny upon request, and maintain audit documentation ( Articles 26,37,40).Those failing to conduct assessments or mitigate uncovered risks face substantial fines, blacklisting and potential service bans (Articles 73, 74).Due diligence obligations ( Articles 14,16,20,[24][25][26][27][34][35] The DSA establishes a graduated set of responsibilities and due diligence duties for online intermediaries based on their role and capacity to cause or mitigate societal risks.Mere conduit intermediaries have minimal obligations beyond transparency (Article 4).",
    "Hosting services must comply with notice-and-action procedures for illegal content (Article 16), inform authorities about detected illegal activities (Article 18), and provide annual transparency reports on content moderation activities (Article 15).",
    "Online platforms additionally need to implement complaint and redress mechanisms for content moderation disputes (Articles 20-21)."
